09/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Monday (9 June), foreign ministers of countries participating in the Southeast European Co-operation Process (SEECP) will hold their first meeting under the chairmanship of BiH. 
Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic will host the summit. 
He is expected to sign an agreement with Greece on co-operation in the fields of culture, education and science. 
Ivanic will sign a similar bilateral accord with Bulgaria and a transport policy document with Albania. 
BiH took over the chairmanship of SEECP from Serbia-Montenegro in April.
In other news, the US government is donating $2.5m to bring electricity to about 400 houses in Zeleni Jadar, in southern BiH. 
Norway has also pledged assistance to the project. 
(Dnevni Avaz - 09/06/03; Onasa, BBC - 08/06/03)
